00:28:39,990 --> 00:28:42,810
But when you're thinking
about a media world,

721
00:28:42,810 --> 00:28:44,460
this can also be very different

722
00:28:44,460 --> 00:28:47,460
if you're designing a 24 by
seven channel for example,

723
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:49,023
and those event based channels.

724
00:28:50,070 --> 00:28:51,420
And the other important part

725
00:28:51,420 --> 00:28:54,510
is you've got the task of
really balancing the cost

726
00:28:54,510 --> 00:28:56,960
and how much resilience
is really enough for you.

727
00:28:58,080 --> 00:29:01,260
If your platform fails entirely,

728
00:29:01,260 --> 00:29:03,490
users will be unable
to consume your content

729
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,150
and this might impact you in other ways

730
00:29:06,150 --> 00:29:07,830
such as increased customer contact

731
00:29:07,830 --> 00:29:09,453
or maybe even financially too.

732
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:12,240
For live events especially,

733
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:14,790
there's no real second
chance, we'll try again later,

734
00:29:14,790 --> 00:29:16,740
that moment's just simply gone forever.

735
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:23,007
Like we discussed, things can go wrong.

736
00:29:23,007 --> 00:29:24,840
So redundancy is really critical

737
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:26,610
to keep your stream up and running

738
00:29:26,610 --> 00:29:29,573
