00:41:58,560 --> 00:42:01,920
and handle unpredictable traffic spikes,

1048
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:05,730
all while maintaining strong
security and compliance.

1049
00:42:05,730 --> 00:42:08,760
Additionally, unlike many
national distributors

1050
00:42:08,760 --> 00:42:12,810
who receive SRT feeds and
then retransmit those,

1051
00:42:12,810 --> 00:42:16,470
at NESN, we control every
step of the broadcast.

1052
00:42:16,470 --> 00:42:18,750
First, the game is captured by cameras,

1053
00:42:18,750 --> 00:42:21,360
which are connected to our
mobile production unit,

1054
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:23,100
otherwise known as the truck.

1055
00:42:23,100 --> 00:42:24,780
It's an actual truck

1056
00:42:24,780 --> 00:42:27,700
with the production equipment inside it.

1057
00:42:27,700 --> 00:42:30,570
We have 4K cameras and HD cameras

1058
00:42:30,570 --> 00:42:32,580
at Fenway Park for the Red Sox

1059
00:42:32,580 --> 00:42:35,310
and at TD Garden for the Bruins.

1060
00:42:35,310 --> 00:42:36,143
For away games,

1061
00:42:36,143 --> 00:42:39,870
we have our own HD cameras
that travel with the teams.

1062
00:42:39,870 --> 00:42:43,110
The feed is then relayed over
the internet from the truck

1063
00:42:43,110 --> 00:42:44,730
or from the opponent's stadiums

1064
00:42:44,730 --> 00:42:47,340
to master control at our Boston office.

1065
00:42:47,340 --> 00:42:51,090
These feeds are shared directly
with our linear distributors

1066
00:42:51,090 --> 00:42:54,030
for fans still watching
sports the old fashioned way

1067
00:42:54,030 --> 00:42:56,220
through their cable subscriptions.

1068
00:42:56,220 --> 00:43:00,420
And additionally, the SRT
feed is routed directly to AWS

1069
00:43:00,420 --> 00:43:03,213
through AWS hardware encoders.

1070
00:43:04,350 --> 00:43:08,070
About 50% of the Red Sox
and Bruins seasons games

1071
00:43:08,070 --> 00:43:09,480
are home games,

1072
00:43:09,480 --> 00:43:13,098
which we offer in HD and 4K.

1073
00:43:13,098 --> 00:43:15,120
AWS makes it easy for us

1074
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:18,330
to manage the availability
of our 4K stream

1075
00:43:18,330 --> 00:43:21,450
using an AWS elemental encoder

1076
00:43:21,450 --> 00:43:25,440
via Media Live for transcoding
and streaming management.

1077
00:43:25,440 --> 00:43:26,790
We installed Media live

1078
00:43:26,790 --> 00:43:31,680
anywhere on our AWS Elemental
encoder with John's help

1079
00:43:31,680 --> 00:43:34,830
so that we could administer
the feed through Media live

1080
00:43:34,830 --> 00:43:38,190
the same way we manage
our HD and UHD links

1081
00:43:38,190 --> 00:43:40,680
in the media live dashboard.

1082
00:43:40,680 --> 00:43:44,520
From the 4K source, we configured
a media live output group

1083
00:43:44,520 --> 00:43:49,520
that contains 4K, 2K, 1080p,
and 720p video outputs,

1084
00:43:50,520 --> 00:43:53,141
as well as stereo and
surround audio outputs

1085
00:43:53,141 --> 00:43:56,190
and closed caption outputs.

1086
00:43:56,190 --> 00:43:58,409
We kept the traffic...

1087
00:43:58,409 --> 00:44:01,440
Sorry, we kept the audio
and video tracks separate

1088
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:03,480
because we found that maxing

1089
00:44:03,480 --> 00:44:07,770
resulted in issues with
some of the OTT players.

1090
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:10,830
We used a media package V2 channel group

1091
00:44:10,830 --> 00:44:14,280
to create Dash and HLS origin endpoints,

1092
00:44:14,280 --> 00:44:18,240
again, for compatibility
on different systems.

1093
00:44:18,240 --> 00:44:19,530
And those origins

1094
00:44:19,530 --> 00:44:22,620
are then used for
CloudFront distributions.

1095
00:44:22,620 --> 00:44:24,690
A major advantage to using CloudFront

1096
00:44:24,690 --> 00:44:26,580
is that it automatically scales

1097
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:30,300
to accommodate traffic variations.

1098
00:44:30,300 --> 00:44:32,760
So for example, if the Sox
are playing the Yankees,

1099
00:44:32,760 --> 00:44:35,280
we don't have to worry
about edge capacity,

1100
00:44:35,280 --> 00:44:37,413
CloudFront takes care of that for us.

1101
00:44:38,940 --> 00:44:41,430
We also occasionally get third party feeds

1102
00:44:41,430 --> 00:44:43,110
or one-off direct feeds

1103
00:44:43,110 --> 00:44:46,470
like batting practice
directly from Fenway Park

1104
00:44:46,470 --> 00:44:49,620
or morning skate from
Bruins Practice Arena

1105
00:44:49,620 --> 00:44:52,440
that we offer as digital exclusives.

1106
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:57,330
And we have an HD link that we
use for those one-off events.

1107
00:44:57,330 --> 00:45:00,390
We use the same basic
flow for those events.

1108
00:45:00,390 --> 00:45:02,100
The live or third party feed

1109
00:45:02,100 --> 00:45:04,290
is rolled out through the HD link,

1110
00:45:04,290 --> 00:45:08,220
and the HD feed is transcoded
into lower output tiers

1111
00:45:08,220 --> 00:45:12,060
to accommodate CTV and mobile devices.

1112
00:45:12,060 --> 00:45:13,680
Then it's the same Media live

1113
00:45:13,680 --> 00:45:15,933
to Media package to CloudFront Flow.

1114
00:45:17,250 --> 00:45:20,580
Additionally, CloudFront
logs across all services

1115
00:45:20,580 --> 00:45:22,410
provide metrics and alarms

1116
00:45:22,410 --> 00:45:25,650
that help detect performance issues early,

1117
00:45:25,650 --> 00:45:27,330
maintain stream quality,

1118
00:45:27,330 --> 00:45:29,490
and ensure smooth delivery.

1119
00:45:29,490 --> 00:45:30,870
Having these logs

1120
00:45:30,870 --> 00:45:34,800
easily accessible and
queryable using Log Insights

1121
00:45:34,800 --> 00:45:38,433
is essential to a lean
digital team like ours.

1122
00:45:39,810 --> 00:45:43,320
In summary, CloudFront empowers NESN

1123
00:45:43,320 --> 00:45:47,040
to deliver reliable high
quality streams for every fan,

1124
00:45:47,040 --> 00:45:50,370
scale seamlessly during live sports peaks,

1125
00:45:50,370 --> 00:45:54,120
protect media rights and
maintain regulatory compliance,

1126
00:45:54,120 --> 00:45:55,890
and gain real time insights

1127
00:45:55,890 --> 00:45:58,533
into audience behavior and performance.

