1135
00:46:15,580 --> 00:46:18,330
MediaTailor is a managed service

1136
00:46:18,330 --> 00:46:19,740
under the Elemental umbrella

1137
00:46:19,740 --> 00:46:24,420
that does ad replacement and
ad insertion for live streams

1138
00:46:24,420 --> 00:46:26,043
or on-demand streams, actually.

1139
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:30,401
And this workflow here,
again, it uses MediaTailor,

1140
00:46:30,401 --> 00:46:33,300
but a lot of the other
ad insertion platforms

1141
00:46:33,300 --> 00:46:35,160
work in a similar manner.

1142
00:46:35,160 --> 00:46:36,940
When you're trying to
monetize your streams,

1143
00:46:36,940 --> 00:46:39,213
it adds a whole new set of challenges.

1144
00:46:41,700 --> 00:46:43,100
In effect of...

1145
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:45,510
This is called dynamic ad insertion.

1146
00:46:45,510 --> 00:46:50,250
And just by the name, you add
a dynamic element into it.

1147
00:46:50,250 --> 00:46:53,010
Every single manifests for
end users are personalized

1148
00:46:53,010 --> 00:46:55,350
because they have ads
destined for that end user.

1149
00:46:55,350 --> 00:46:57,060
Whether you're using linear ads

1150
00:46:57,060 --> 00:46:58,710
or whether you're using
some of the newer formats

1151
00:46:58,710 --> 00:47:00,900
like Squeeze Back or Pause Ads.

1152
00:47:00,900 --> 00:47:02,850
So before, we've always
talked about scaling

1153
00:47:02,850 --> 00:47:04,860
and CloudFront scaling the origin.

1154
00:47:04,860 --> 00:47:06,630
When we talk about ad insertion,

1155
00:47:06,630 --> 00:47:08,520
the origin becomes that
much more important

1156
00:47:08,520 --> 00:47:10,530
because every single
request from the end user,

1157
00:47:10,530 --> 00:47:12,210
whether you have a thousand
or a million users,

1158
00:47:12,210 --> 00:47:13,617
are going directly to the origin,

1159
00:47:13,617 --> 00:47:16,830
and the origin's modifying
the manifest in real time.

1160
00:47:16,830 --> 00:47:17,820
So it's really important

1161
00:47:17,820 --> 00:47:22,409
that your origin can scale with
your viewers appropriately.

1162
00:47:22,409 --> 00:47:25,050
When you configure a
CloudFront for advertising,

1163
00:47:25,050 --> 00:47:27,960
you're gonna have a couple more
behaviors being configured.

1164
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:30,359
For your manifest, you're
no longer caching that,

1165
00:47:30,359 --> 00:47:32,817
you're sending them directly
to the origin server,

1166
00:47:32,817 --> 00:47:35,250
which is then modifying
every single manifest

1167
00:47:35,250 --> 00:47:36,900
going to the end user.

1168
00:47:36,900 --> 00:47:39,570
Then the MediaTailor in this case

1169
00:47:39,570 --> 00:47:42,390
is going to make a call
to an advertiser upstream,

1170
00:47:42,390 --> 00:47:44,340
whether it's Spring Surf, Freewill,

1171
00:47:44,340 --> 00:47:46,650
any of those ad platforms.

1172
00:47:46,650 --> 00:47:48,120
And those must scale as well

1173
00:47:48,120 --> 00:47:49,260
because every single request

1174
00:47:49,260 --> 00:47:51,543
is gonna be a unique
request to an ad server.

1175
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:54,229
So it's really important

1176
00:47:54,229 --> 00:47:56,489
when we add dynamic ad
insertion into a platform

1177
00:47:56,489 --> 00:47:59,250
that we look into that as an origin.

1178
00:47:59,250 --> 00:48:00,560
As well as DRM platforms as well,

1179
00:48:00,560 --> 00:48:04,471
you know, they're typically
not behind CloudFront.

1180
00:48:04,471 --> 00:48:06,981
MediaTailor's actually
recently added some features

1181
00:48:06,981 --> 00:48:09,870
to help with the ad platform,

1182
00:48:09,870 --> 00:48:12,049
'cause if everybody's going to
an ad break at the same time

1183
00:48:12,049 --> 00:48:13,652
and we're hitting a million viewers

1184
00:48:13,652 --> 00:48:15,900
to an ad platform all at once,

1185
00:48:15,900 --> 00:48:19,260
the ad platform, whoever it
might be, can't handle that.

1186
00:48:19,260 --> 00:48:20,980
So MediaTailor actually has the ability

1187
00:48:20,980 --> 00:48:23,340
to pre-fetch ads before an ad break

1188
00:48:23,340 --> 00:48:25,740
and stack a request to an ad server.

1189
00:48:25,740 --> 00:48:27,600
So these are some of the
really important considerations

1190
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:29,910
when you're adding monetization
to your live stream.

1191
00:48:29,910 --> 00:48:32,880
Again, whether it's linear ad replacement,

1192
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:36,150
overlay, squeeze back,
any of the newer formats,

1193
00:48:36,150 --> 00:48:37,800
there's a lot more considerations

